🔹 MEASURE 1: Net Sales
👉 What it means
Total revenue from sales.
🛠 Steps
1.	Right-click Sales table
2.	Click New Measure
3.	Type:
Net Sales = SUM(Sales[SalesAmount])
✔ Press Enter
________________________________________
🔹 MEASURE 2: Total Cost
Total Cost = SUM(Sales[Cost])
________________________________________
🔹 MEASURE 3: Gross Margin (GM)
👉 Profit value
Gross Margin = [Net Sales] - [Total Cost]
________________________________________
🔹 MEASURE 4: Gross Margin %
👉 Profit percentage
GM % = DIVIDE([Gross Margin], [Net Sales], 0)
📌 Format → Percentage (2 decimals)
________________________________________
🔹 MEASURE 5: Total Orders
Total Orders = DISTINCTCOUNT(Sales[OrderID])
________________________________________
🔹 MEASURE 6: Total Visits
Total Visits = SUM(Sales[Visits])
________________________________________
🔹 MEASURE 7: Conversion Rate %
👉 Orders ÷ Visits
Conversion Rate % = 
DIVIDE([Total Orders], [Total Visits], 0)
📌 Format → Percentage
________________________________________
🔹 MEASURE 8: Net Sales YTD (Year-to-Date)
👉 You MUST have a Date table
Step A: Create Date Table
DateTable = 
ADDCOLUMNS(
    CALENDAR (DATE(2020,1,1), DATE(2030,12,31)),
    "Year", YEAR([Date]),
    "Month", FORMAT([Date], "MMM")
)
Step B: Relate Date → Sales[Date]
Step C: YTD Measure
Net Sales YTD =
TOTALYTD(
    [Net Sales],
    DateTable[Date]
)
________________________________________
🔹 MEASURE 9: Net Sales YoY Growth %
Net Sales YoY % =
VAR PrevYearSales =
    CALCULATE(
        [Net Sales],
        SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(DateTable[Date])
    )
RETURN
DIVIDE([Net Sales] - PrevYearSales, PrevYearSales, 0)
📌 Format → Percentage
________________________________________
🔹 MEASURE 10: Contribution %
👉 Share of total sales
Contribution % =
DIVIDE(
    [Net Sales],
    CALCULATE([Net Sales], ALL(Sales)),
    0)________________________________________
