🎯 Aim
To create essential DAX measures in Microsoft Power BI Desktop for sales analysis, including revenue, cost, profit, conversion metrics, and time-intelligence calculations (YTD and YoY).
________________________________________
🧭 Algorithm (12 Points)
1.	Open Microsoft Power BI Desktop and load the Sales dataset using Home → Get Data.
2.	Go to Report View and open the Fields pane.
3.	Right-click the Sales table and choose New Measure.
4.	Create Net Sales measure using SUM(Sales[SalesAmount]).
5.	Create Total Cost measure using SUM(Sales[Cost]).
6.	Create Gross Margin using [Net Sales] - [Total Cost].
7.	Create GM % using DIVIDE([Gross Margin], [Net Sales], 0) and format as Percentage.
8.	Create Total Orders using DISTINCTCOUNT(Sales[OrderID]).
9.	Create Total Visits using SUM(Sales[Visits]) and Conversion Rate % using Orders ÷ Visits.
10.	Create a Date Table using CALENDAR and relate it to Sales[Date].
11.	Create Net Sales YTD using TOTALYTD([Net Sales], DateTable[Date]).
12.	Create Net Sales YoY % and Contribution % using time-intelligence and ALL function for total share calculation.

